com.hazelcast.util.scheduler

Class SecondsBasedEntryTaskScheduler<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.util.scheduler.SecondsBasedEntryTaskScheduler<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - entry key type
    V - entry value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntryTaskScheduler<K,V>

    public final class SecondsBasedEntryTaskScheduler<K,V>
extends Object
implements EntryTaskScheduler<K,V>
    Schedule execution of an entry for seconds later. This is similar to a scheduled executor service, but instead of scheduling a execution for a specific millisecond, this service will schedule it with second proximity. For example, if delayMillis is 600 ms, then the entry will be scheduled to execute in 1 second. If delayMillis is 2400, then the entry will be scheduled to execute in 3 seconds. Therefore, delayMillis is ceil-ed to the next second. It gives up exact time scheduling to gain the power of: a) bulk execution of all operations within the same second or b) being able to reschedule (postpone) execution.
